<p>My application uses Entity Framework as Data Access Layer and WCF for communication and DTO objects.</p>  <p>What is the best practice for sending Lambda expression from client to server  in order to dynamically querying database using LINQ To Entity?</p>  <p><strong>Update:</strong></p>  <p>An example:</p>  <p>Assume that there are flowing classes in server application</p>  <pre><code>// Data Access Class public class PersonService {     public List&lt;Person&gt; GetPersons(Expression&lt;Func&lt;PersonDto, bool&gt;&gt; expression)     {         var persons = Db.Set&lt;Person&gt;();         return persons.Where(expression).ToList();     } }  // WCF Class public class PersonWcfService : IPersonWcfService {     public List&lt;PersonDto&gt; GetPersons(Expression&lt;Func&lt;PersonDto, bool&gt;&gt; expression)     {         var personService = new PersonService();         return ToDtoList(personService.GetPerson(expression));     } } </code></pre>  <p>The <code>GetPerson</code> method filters and returns a list of <code>Person</code> based on <code>expression</code> parameter.</p>  <p>The code in client application may be like this:</p>  <pre><code>Expression&lt;Func&lt;PersonDto, bool&gt;&gt; exp = x =&gt; x.Name.Contains("John"); var personWcfService = new PersonWcfService(); var persons = personWcfService.GetPersons(exp); </code></pre>  <p>Since we cant use Lamda expression directly in WCF services, What is the beset practice for sending <code>expression</code> from client application to server through WCF services?</p>